[ProMED-mail thanks Karsten Nockler and Edoardo Pozio for this information.

Wild boar is a well known source of _Trichinella_ in Europe. It is not clear from the text whether the wild boar meat was deliberately introduced without proper veterinary control or whether it was by accident. So far, no human cases have been registered. - Mod.EP]

